### Requirements
> `Python >= 3.7`

### 1. Installation


```bash
$ pip install Interphase
```

### 2. Quick Start


#### ğŸ“  Simple folder structure
```
ğŸ“  your_project
|
â”œâ”€â”€ğŸ“ types (requied)
|   |
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ğŸ“„api.d.ts (optional)
|
â””â”€â”€ğŸ“„main.py
```


#### ğŸ“„main.py
```python
from Interphase import Interphase

ts = Interphase("./types")

userData = {
    "name": "John Doe",
    "age": 30,
    "email": "example@demo.com",
    "skills": ["Python", "TypeScript", "JavaScript"]
}

ts.write('api', 'UserData', userData)
```

#### ğŸ“„ api.d.ts
```typescript
export type UserData = {
    name: string;
    age: number;
    email: string;
    skills: string[];
}
```


### 3. Real Life Developer Usage


#### .gitmodules

```toml
[submodule "api"]
	path = api
	url = https://github.com/username/api.git
```

